content.description: Climb the low angle dike for about 15 feet to the bulge. One or two moves gets you through the crux and on to easier terrain. Continue up the crack system to the slab above. One bolt high on the slab leads you to chain anchors.
content.protection: Protect the crux with .2-.75 X4 or Camalots, gear to one inch for the rest.
content.location: On the far right side of Toon Town. Look for the bulge with crack system and then slab above.

content.description: 15 feet of fun finger crack leads to easy climbing up high. Check out the cool tunnel feature from above.
content.protection: Gear to 1". 2 bolts with rap rings at the top (no chains)
content.location: Look for a finger crack that starts on a ledge. There's a little way trail to gain the ledge from the right side of the crag.

content.description: Climb up towards the corner feature to a bolt protected crux. A few fun moves gets you past to easier climbing. Chain anchors up top.
content.protection: Mostly small cams and nuts. Pro to 1 inch. One bolt at the crux on the face to the right of the corner.
content.location: Look for the corner feature and the dike above it.

content.description: Follow the right leaning crack / slab to a roof. Gain the roof for easy climbing to the top.
content.protection: Gear to 2". 2 bolts with chains for anchor.
content.location: To the right of both Elmer Fudge and Buzzed Bunny, on the right of the shrub-topped bulge. Look for an arching crack that goes right to a roof. You should be able to see the anchor chains from the ground.

climbs.name: Elmer Fudge
climbs.fa: Ron Cotman, Sean Woods, Viktor Kramar 2010

content.description: Dirty start to fun crack climbing to slab.
content.protection: Gear to 1", 1 bolt. 2 bolts with chains at the top.
content.location: Far left route on the wall. Look for a dirty gully start to cracks above. See if you can find the roof for Buzzed Bunny; this is the route just to the left of that.

content.description: Climb up to veer right away from Elmer Fudge. Follow the right leaning crack and slab to the fixed pin in the wide crack. Move out left on the slab and finish on Elmer Fudge anchors.
